CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1964, pg. 3, reads: "Wishing - Samuel Wolfolk and Jimmy Harris look longingly at an autographed baseball, held by Bill Nunn, Courier sports editor.  The precious disk bears the signature of Willie Mays.  It will be given as first prize, in addition to the transistor radio.  Bill, himself, may be at the park K-Day to award the baseball - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Samuel Wolfolk and Jimmy Harris looking at baseball signed by Willie Mays held by Bill Nunn Jr., in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper office
